article.headline: SMU tops Georgetown 81-73 behind McMurray's 19

images.name: McClung with no-look dime
images.caption: Georgetown's Mac McClung hits Jessie Govan with a no-look pass, leading to a tough and-1 bucket.

article.story: WASHINGTON -- Jahmal McMurray scored 19 points, Isiaha Mike and Ethan Chargois had 17 apiece and SMU defeated Georgetown 81-73 on Saturday. McMurray had four 3-pointers and Chargois three as the Mustangs (7-4) went 10 of 25 from distance while the Hoyas (7-3) were 4 of 18. SMU went on a 15-2 run with Nat Dixon, who started it with two 3-pointers, scoring all 11 of his points for a 23-17 lead. The Mustangs never trailed after that. McMurray converted all three free throws in the final minute for a 39-34 halftime lead and hit a 3 as the Mustangs scored the first five of the second half. The lead was 11 when the Hoyas reeled off 11 straight and it stayed close the rest of the way. SMU made 5 of 6 from the foul line in the final minute while Georgetown, which shot 40 percent for the game, missed its last three shots and was 1 of 8 in the final six minutes. Jessie Govan had 17 and James Akinjo 16 for Georgetown. It was only the second meeting ever, the first coming in the second round of the 1984 NCAA Tournament in Pullman, Washington, when the Hoyas won 37-36 behind current coach Patrick Ewing's 10 points.

videos.headline: Foster cuts to basket for slam
videos.description: SMU's Ethan Chargois finds the cutting Jarrey Foster, who slams it home for the easy dunk.

videos.headline: Hunt catches alley-oop off turnover
videos.description: SMU capitalizes on Georgetown's turnover with an alley-oop from Jimmy Whitt Jr. to Feron Hunt.

videos.headline: Akinjo makes defender fall
videos.description: Georgetown's James Akinjo drops SMU's Isiaha Mike with a quick hesitation and gets the ball to Trey Mourning for an easy lay in.
